  <div class="wp-page-content">
    <p>Welcome! If you're not family, a close friend or part of my Georgetown Digital Marketing class, then I am humbled you're viewing my website. In this current iteration, Maxweinerb.com is meant to support my blogs as part of my school work. In the coming months you can expect a combination of personal posts (ie. Simple lasagna recipe) and professional more business oriented posts (coming soon!).</p>
    <p>Now for a quick, generic about me; I obviously like cooking, eating, traveling, biking outdoors and long walks on the beach. I graduated from University of Michigan and spent one year freezing in Chicago (Polar Vortex 14') before moving back to where I grew up, Washington, DC. I've spent the last 5 years working in Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) startups in variety of industries while wearing a few different hats.</p>
    <p>Get ready – I am moving to Spain in September 19' and anticipate this blog to take on a new life while abroad.</p>
    <blockquote>No One Has As Much Fun As People – Unknown</blockquote>
